description: The geomorphological map contains the enclosing polygons of places with similar soil forms. Geomorphological map based on the analysis of multibeam bathymetric data on soil structures and their classification according to length and height of the soil forms. The map is subdivided into the following classes: slopes, little cliffs, large dunes, small to medium-sized dunes, irregular bottom structure (dredge material, abrasion), dredging tracks and soil surface without structure.
name: Geomorphological map (Lower Sea Scheldt, 2010)
